The paper discusses the use of deep learning models for various tasks such as speech recognition, image classification, natural language processing, and bioinformatics, which are all related to machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper specifically focuses on replacing the softmax layer with a linear support vector machine, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning and optimization. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of neural nets and SVMs, which are also related to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-categories, respectively.
